Definition:
Concurrency is about managing multiple tasks simultaneously.
Tasks may not actually run at the same time but make progress by interleaving execution (time-slicing) on a single or multiple cores.

Analogy: Single chef working on multiple dishes,switching between them to make progress on all.

Use Concurrency:
When you need tasks to interact (e.g., producer-consumer patterns).
For responsive user interfaces or managing background tasks.
Example: A server handling multiple client requests simultaneously.
